questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direction: &lt;/strong&gt;Study the pie - chart and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In an institute, there are 900 students who use different modes of transport for to and from travel. The given pie diagram represents the requisite data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/04/DI_07-04-2021_Vaibhav%20soni_umesh_D%205.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 245px; height: 301px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The number of students who travel on foot is:&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The total number of students who use different modes of transport for to and from travel = 900&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The number of students who travel on the Foot = 70&amp;deg;/360&amp;deg; &amp;times; 900&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 70&amp;deg;/360&amp;deg; &amp;times; 900&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rArr; 175&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Source of funds from Toll = 4500&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agent&amp;rsquo;s commission = 10%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After taking out his commission;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(100 - 10)% = 4500&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;90% = 4500&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 100% = (4500/90%) &amp;times; 100%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 5000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The agent need to collect Rs. 5000 as toll.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;The given pie chart shows the marks scored by a student in different subjects- Hindi, English, Maths, Science, social science in an exam. The values are given in degree and the total marks are 900.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/03/605032dfe78fd8d0a77ec0df_Vikash%20Kumar_Sanyukta%20Gaikar_19.03.21_D1.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 248px; height: 327px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What are the marks obtained by the student in Hindi?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total marks = 900&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept used: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The total angle formed at&amp;nbsp;the point is 360&amp;deg;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;360&amp;deg; = 900 marks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The angle made by subject Hindi on the pie chart = 70&amp;deg;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;360&amp;deg; = 900&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 1&amp;deg; = 900/360&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 70&amp;deg; =&amp;nbsp;(900/360)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 70 = 175&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The marks obtained by the student in Hindi is 175&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the Graph,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total sales of shirts = Rs 20000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Highest selling size of shirts are XS and M = 35% and 24%&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lowest Selling size of shirts are XL and XXS = 6% and 9%&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

